All applications under this project will follow the following rules..

# PYTHON

- All backend code will be implemented using Python and the FastAPI library

## Coding Standards

- Use uv for all dependency management (uv add, uv run, uv sync)
- Always use type hints with sdk types
- Follow PEP 8 and Black formatting
- Never hardcode credentials - use environment variables
- Write docstrings for public APIs
- Use descriptive variable names
- Write defensive code with proper error handling
- Test new features with pytest
- Use Python 3.10+ features
- Log API calls with request context

## API Standards

- Use FastAPI's automatic OpenAPI documentation
- Document all endpoints with docstrings
- Use proper HTTP status codes
- Follow REST conventions for resource naming
- Generate TypeScript/JavaScript clients from OpenAPI spec